@@lSwift Line Marker One@@N~
In Swift Line Marker One, practical survival and legal formality occupy the same narrow ground.  Keeper survey scars appear intermittently, some useful and some dangerously misleading.  Footfalls alternate between hard ring and brittle crumble as crust thickness changes without warning.  Dawn and dusk draw most crossings, when reflection weakens enough for marker lines to reappear.  Three usable linesâeast, south, and westâpull traffic in competing directions.
