conversion tables~
Bronze inlay lines mark ratio columns that converted inland water debt into maritime risk charges. Later clerks scratched corrective entries between the lines when harbor rates shifted, producing a dense lattice of arithmetic and seal marks. A note near the threshold warns assessors never to apply wet-seal rates to funerary cargo.
~
