inspection dais~
The inspection dais is scored by countless crate drags and fitted with shallow channels to collect residue from opened relic containers. Carved labels around each channel identify hazard classes, from inert funerary dust to volatile ritual compounds. A faded warning states that provenance disputes must be settled before any lid is broken.
~
